@graph.dc:description: Declaring Class: org.w3.ldp.testsuite.test.BasicContainerTest - LDP servers that successfully create a resource from a RDF representation in the request entity body MUST honor the client's requested interaction model(s). The created resource can be thought of as an RDF named graph [rdf11-concepts]. If any model cannot be honored, the server MUST fail the request.
